<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">□&nbsp;Overwatch&nbsp;Command&nbsp;Meeting&nbsp;Log&nbsp;&nbsp;□</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<div style="border:solid 1px #000000; color:#000000; border-radius: 10px; background:#c9c9c9; padding:5px; margin-bottom: 10px; padding:10px">
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p><span style="font-size:140%;"><strong>Overwatch Command Meeting Log</strong></span><br />
L05-Eyes Only</p>
</div>
<hr />
<p><strong>Date:</strong> 2019/11/11 @ 11:02<br />
<strong>Present:</strong> O5-01, O5-02, O5-03, O5-04, O5-06, O5-07, O5-08, O5-09, O5-11, O5-12<br />
<strong>Virtual:</strong> O5-05, O5-10<br />
<strong>Absent:</strong> O5-13<br />
<strong>Agenda:</strong> <em>The Kelipat Nogah Initiative.</em></p>
<hr />
<p>[BEGIN LOG]</p>
<p><strong>O5-01:</strong> I don't think this will take very long, but I thank you all for attending. I assume that everyone's had a chance to look over the impact study provided by Dr. Low?</p>
<p><strong>O5-12:</strong> I believe so. I find it concerning that none of us have been aware of the extent the Sarkic threat poses until now, however.</p>
<p><strong>O5-08:</strong> I disagree. We've heard rumblings from those flesh cultists before, this is nothing new. I think that Dr. Low is either working too hard and seeing threats where there are none, or this is just a blatant power grab. Frankly, I am more inclined to believe the latter. She's gone too-</p>
<p><strong>O5-12:</strong> <em>[interrupting]</em> That's enough. This is neither the time nor the place for you to bring up your past issues with her. Your animosity blunted the success of Project Sitra Achra and we all know it.</p>
<p><strong>O5-08:</strong> Sitra Achra was a mistake. Giving that much access to the GOC was a mistake. We've got a tenuous enough relationship with the UN, and allowing them to get an even better understanding of the scope of our operations has only emboldened the elements in the UN that want to shut us down.</p>
<p><strong>O5-03:</strong> Oh come on, Eight. You may think that your position on Overwatch grants you unlimited power, but that's not what the Charter is for. Your blustering and belly-aching doesn't-</p>
<p><strong>O5-08:</strong> I didn't come here to be insulted by someone who only pretends to be my peer.</p>
<p><strong>O5-01:</strong> <em>[Gavel]</em> ENOUGH. Bickering amongst ourselves won't solve a damn thing. The fact of the matter is is that Dr. Low is merely the messenger here. All of her analysts agree, the independent analysis provided by Twelve's Overwatch Committee also agrees. The Sarkic threat has gotten too big to ignore, and something must be done.</p>
<p><strong>O5-12:</strong> My analysts do agree that-</p>
<p><strong>O5-08:</strong> Of course they would.</p>
<p><strong>O5-12:</strong> Look. You may resent Dr. Low, and you may resent my position within this body, but that doesn't change the fact that I am a member of this body, and it sure as hell doesn't change the fact that these reports exist. Did you even read them?</p>
<p><strong>O5-08:</strong> To be frank? I didn't bother. Dr. Low has been fear mongering ever since she got her promotion to L03. This so-called &quot;Sarkic Threat&quot; of hers has been a dirge she's been playing for years, and quite frankly, I'm tired of it. We've poured hundreds of millions of dollars down the Sitra Achra drain, and I'm done with it.</p>
<p><strong>O5-03:</strong> That's rich, coming from you. How much money got pumped into SCP-████ before we decided that it just wasn't going to do what you want, despite how much you wanted it to?</p>
<p><strong>O5-08:</strong> So now we're gonna talk about that? What about SCP-</p>
<p><strong>O5-01:</strong> <em>[Gavel]</em> Gentlemen, please. If either of you step outside the scope of this meeting again, I will have you censured. By a show of hands, who here has actually read the report provided by Dr. Low?</p>
<p><em>[The sound of rustling and movement can be heard.]</em></p>
<p><strong>O5-01:</strong> That is more than enough to meet quorum. Call the vote.</p>
